South Korean President  Lee Myung Bak 
said a new era in inter-Korean relations can be opened if  North
Korea  begins behaving sincerely. Lee, speaking in a New Year
address broadcast live in  South Korea , said his government will
strive for peace on the divided Korean peninsula, while it will
respond strongly to any provocation from the North.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sangwon Yoon in  Seoul  at 
